I need to learn to not live in the good times/things of yesterday, but the blessings that God has in store for me today. He does not want you living in what was but what is. Have you been doing this?

God is so amazing! He has truly been testing my faith in Him. I'm driving to a golf tournament and I do not know where exactly it is at. My GPS is telling me where to go and so I follow. On the route a sign appears stating "bridge closed". But I continue to go on the designated route. A few miles down another sign says "closed bridge-residents only". I think to myself... If I turn back it'll be a 30 minute backtrack and an additional 15 minutes to get to my destination. But not once did I say I'm gonna turn back. When I got to the bridge it was as the signs stated "closed", but there was a little side street that allowed me to continue through to my destination. If you think about it, it's similar to how God works in our lives. We see all these obstacles and begin to lose faith in what God has planned for us. If you just continue down the path you are on, the blessing awaiting you is there for you to receive. The little things God makes you realize when you are actively pressing into Him is just amazing. #itisWRITTEN #austin #vaalercreek

Another weekend well spent with this one. She came for the house warming and then stayed for Easter Sunday! Sometimes you have to set back and take it all in. It has been about 2.5 months since we first started our journey to where we are now. We were both slightly broken and had our walls up to some degree. You continue to show me that those walls never needed to be put up in the first place because I am made new and made whole in our Lord Jesus Christ and the love our one true Father. God continues to work in us individually and together and I look forward to the journey as we grow in Him. Let me finish by saying she drove a total of 20 hours to spend the weekend with family friends, and myself. If I don't see that is something special, please slap me. But I know how blessed I am to have her and will continue to show her how thankful I am❤️. #iKNOW #myAhava #itisWRITTEN #HeisRisen #housewarming #Easter

As i sit here and reflect on this past weekend, i am filled with so much joy and love. This youth group has played a vital part of my walk with Jesus. When things are great they are there to celebrate with and when things are rough they are there to lift me up in prayer and encouragement. i knew God was going to show up and do something so great! Lives were changed, chains were broken, addictions were overcome, anger, hurt, frustration, confusion, guilt, shame, and emptiness were all laid at the feet of Jesus. When you can love God and His people through the storms of life, you grow. To choose to say this isn’t it, it’s not over, there is so much more for me means you stand firm in what He has told you and what you know.
This group fight here. This.Is.Us. There will be moments in life where God takes you to the next level. This is it. A group that loves one another no matter what. We show up and lift each other up. We don’t do this alone. God is all about togetherness. I am excited for what God is going to do in all of us and through all of us! Love each and every one of these beautiful and courageous people. #this #is #us

This is not everyone from @passion268 2018, but every single one of the amazing people I got to experience this with is family! 2018 will be a year of great triumphs and blessings in each and every life. We can boldly proclaim who God says we are and grow with each other. That means holding each other accountable. It’s all good that we came here and got to experience all the great things God has for us, but if we just go back to our lives and get back into the same routine of what we were used to, the enemy wins. The enemy wants to keep you in your comfort ability be side he knows you are a weapon that cannot be matched. You are righteous, chosen, forgiven, redeemed, Holy, loved, perfect, purchased, mighty, wonderful, beautiful, courageous, bold, and above all called by name of our one true God. May 2018 bless each and every one of you and may we continue to challenge and grow one another to be the men and women God has ordained us to be! I love you all very much! ❤️ #family
